# No Emojis Policy

**Do not add emojis** to any code, comments, documentation, commit messages, workflow files, or any other project files unless the user explicitly requests them.

## Guidelines

- Code should be professional and emoji-free
- Comments should be clear and text-only
- Documentation should not include emojis
- Error messages and log output should be plain text
- GitHub Actions workflows should not include emojis
- Release notes and changelogs should be emoji-free unless requested

